      "bezeichnung": "Digital Signal Processing 2",
      "lernziele": "<p>At the end of the module the students are expected to understand the following concepts and be able to apply them to real world signal processing problems:</p><ul><li>Digital Filter Realizations</li><li>Signal Processing Applications</li><li>DFT/FFT Algorithms</li><li>FIR Digital Filter Design</li><li>IIR Digital Filter Design</li><li>Interpolation, Decimation and Oversampling</li></ul>",
      "planinhalt": "<p>The module is structured as follows:</p><ul><li>Digital Filter Realizations</li><li>Signal Processing Applications</li><li>DFT/FFT Algorithms</li><li>FIR Digital Filter Design</li><li>IIR Digital Filter Design</li><li>Interpolation, Decimation and Oversampling</li></ul><p>The book is based on the excellent and freely available book &quot;Introduction to Signal Processing&quot; by Sophocles J. Orfanidis. This book also has a useful website: http://eceweb1.rutgers.edu/~orfanidi/intro2sp/</p>",
